         "id": "SECTION_mesoamerica",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Mathematics in Mesoamerica\n\nThere is no doubt that the Mesoamerican peoples had a robust and highly advanced calendrical system. We also know that although they used a vigesimal numerical system, it was mainly the calendar that was used to measure time (<htcite0>; <htcite1>; <htcite2>). Despite the lack of direct evidence of the use of the vigesimal system, there are indications that they employed a grid system that could have been associated with it, as pointed out by Drs. Ruy D. Díaz and Ximena Catepillán (<htcite3>; <htcite4>).\n\nThis understanding was presented in detail in the *First Steps* section (<htcite5>).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "ced67eaf-7378-4589-9166-07f799969e3e",
                     "text": "Catepillán, Ximena",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "ad11b3b2-8cdf-4d71-9cb7-2ac241850945",
                     "text": "Casares Contreras, Orlando & Cetina, José & Cabrera, Venus Sarahí.",
                     "page": "pp. 34",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2022",
                        "month": "",
